{"id":29345792,"date":"2026-04-30T13:24:47","date_gmt":"2026-04-30T07:54:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/?p=29345792"},"modified":"2026-04-30T13:34:04","modified_gmt":"2026-04-30T08:04:04","slug":"career-after-mba-in-marketing","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing","title":{"rendered":"Career After MBA in Marketing: Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_82_2 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\" style=\"cursor:inherit\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"ez-toc-pull-right ez-toc-btn ez-toc-btn-xs ez-toc-btn-default ez-toc-toggle\" aria-label=\"Toggle Table of Content\"><span class=\"ez-toc-js-icon-con\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #999;color:#999\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/a><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#What_is_an_MBA_in_Marketing_Degree\" >What is an MBA in Marketing Degree?&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#Why_Choose_an_MBA_in_Marketing\" >Why Choose an MBA in Marketing?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#Skills_Needed_for_an_MBA_in_Marketing_Job_Roles\" >Skills Needed for an MBA in Marketing Job Roles&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#MBA_in_Marketing_Job_Roles_Salaries_in_India\" >MBA in Marketing Job Roles &amp; Salaries in India<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#Top_Recruiters_Hiring_MBAs_in_Marketing_in_India\" >Top Recruiters Hiring MBAs in Marketing in India<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#How_to_Plan_Your_Career_Path_After_an_MBA_in_Marketing\" >How to Plan Your Career Path After an MBA in Marketing?<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#Career_Scope_MBA_in_Marketing_vs_Other_MBA_Specializations\" >Career Scope: MBA in Marketing vs Other MBA Specializations&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/career-after-mba-in-marketing\/#FAQs\" >FAQs&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n\n<p>An MBA in Marketing is one of the most popular course options in India\u2019s competitive business landscape in 2026. The program unlocks promising career prospects for graduates in varied sectors. From digital marketing and brand management to market research and sales leadership, course graduates can explore numerous roles that offer competitive pay packages and strong growth potential.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out the various career opportunities after completing an MBA in Marketing and the salary potential for graduates, both freshers and experienced.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"What_is_an_MBA_in_Marketing_Degree\"><\/span><strong>What is an MBA in Marketing Degree?&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Short for Master of Business Administration, an MBA offers a specialization in Marketing, along with many other in-demand disciplines, to postgraduate students. Spanning two years, the course offers learning in customer behavior, strategic brand management, and marketing analytics, among other relevant concepts. Graduates can assume leadership positions such as Marketing Directors and Brand Managers.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Key Highlights of MBA Marketing<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>An MBA in Marketing is designed to equip students with specialized skills\u2014a combination of creative, strategic, and analytical abilities \u2014 that help them drive customer engagement, brand growth, and business success across diverse industries. Detailed below are the major highlights of the program, along with the MBA in Marketing salary in India:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Key Highlights<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Duration<\/td><td>2 years (24 months) \/ 4 semesters<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Job Roles<\/td><td>Public Relations Manager, Digital Marketing Manager, Business Development Manager<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Average MBA in Sales and Marketing Salary<\/td><td>INR 7 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Key Subjects<\/td><td>Marketing Management, Consumer Behavior, E-Marketing&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Top Recruiters<\/td><td>EY, Goldman Sachs, LTIMindtree<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Indeed<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Why_Choose_an_MBA_in_Marketing\"><\/span><strong>Why Choose an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>An MBA in Marketing is the ideal choice for you to learn crucial analytical, strategic, and creative skills that are in high demand in the industry today to drive brand growth. Here are some other reasons to opt for the program:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Strong demand:<\/strong> Various industries such as E-commerce, FMCG, Media, and Consulting are in constant need of qualified, skilled professionals to drive their marketing campaigns and customer engagement. An MBA in Marketing equips you with the right skills for the job.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Diverse roles and lucrative salaries:<\/strong> An MBA in Marketing is also preferred for the wide range of roles it unlocks for graduates\u2014Digital Marketer, Brand Manager, and Sales Strategist. Additionally, the average MBA Marketing salary in India is estimated at INR 22,000-40,000 per month (approx.), commensurate with industry standards.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Enhanced skill set: <\/strong>Students gain a wide range of specialized skills to excel in their career paths\u2014from market research to customer behavior analysis and data-driven decision-making. These skills are in high demand across domains today.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Glassdoor<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Skills_Needed_for_an_MBA_in_Marketing_Job_Roles\"><\/span><strong>Skills Needed for an MBA in Marketing Job Roles&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the most crucial ways to secure a high salary in MBA Marketing jobs is to develop the right set of skills required for the role. An MBA Marketing program syllabus is designed to equip students with the skills to advance their careers. Some of the critical technical proficiencies that students gain in the course are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Technical Skills\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Tools &amp; Technologies<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>SEO &amp; SEM<\/td><td>Ahrefs, SEMrush, Google Ads<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Data Analysis &amp; Reporting<\/td><td>Power BI, MS Excel<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Market Research &amp; Analysis<\/td><td>Tableau, Google Analytics<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Social Media Marketing<\/td><td>Buffer, Hootsuite<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Email Marketing &amp; Customer Relationship Management<\/td><td>HubSpot, Salesforce<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"MBA_in_Marketing_Job_Roles_Salaries_in_India\"><\/span><strong>MBA in Marketing Job Roles &amp; Salaries in India<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>After completing an MBA in Marketing, graduates can apply for jobs in diverse sectors. A few examples include Brand Manager, Marketing Manager, Digital Marketing Specialist, and the like. Salaries may vary for freshers and experienced candidates; however, the average MBA Marketing salary per month in India is roughly INR 28,000. This is indicative and may vary from one organization to another.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For Freshers<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As fresh MBA Marketing graduates, students can join entry-level roles in relevant industries at starting-level pay. The table below shares the details of what freshers can expect after graduation:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Parameters\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><br><br>Job Roles<\/td><td>Market Research Analyst<br>Sales Manager<br>Digital Marketing Executive<br>Business Development Executive<br>Brand Associate<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Salary<\/td><td>INR 3 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Key Skills<\/td><td>Brand Management<br>Data Analytics<br>Customer Behavior Insights<br>Creative Content Creation<br>Data-Driven Decision-Making \u00a0<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Hiring Industries<\/td><td>Finance<br>\u00a0Entertainment<br>Advertising<br>E-Commerce<br>Public Relations\u00a0<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: Glassdoor<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For Experienced<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>For experienced professionals, MBA in Marketing roles typically include Marketing Manager, Brand Manager, and Marketing Director. The MBA in Marketing salary scale, in this case, tends to be higher, especially with increased experience.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Parameters\u00a0<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Description<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><br><br>Job Roles<\/td><td>PR Manager<br>Digital Marketing Manager<br>Business Development Manager<br>Brand Manager<br>Advertising Manager<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Salary&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 13.1 LPA (approx)<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Key Skills<\/td><td>Brand Management<br>Advanced Digital Marketing Analytics<br>Consumer Insight<br>Leading Cross-Functional Teams<br>Financial Acumen for Marketing Budgets<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><br>Hiring Industries<\/td><td>Brand Management<br>Fashion and Retail<br>Tourism and Hospitality<br>Telecommunications<br>FMCG\u00a0<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Source: AmbitionBox<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Government Jobs After an MBA in Marketing Degree<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Government jobs after an MBA in Marketing offer graduates stable career opportunities. These are available in roles such as PR Managers, Marketing Officers, and administrative services across various government departments and PSUs. Listed below are 5 popular government job roles for graduates with an MBA in Marketing, along with their corresponding salaries in India.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\"><thead><tr><th><strong>Job Roles<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Average Annual Salary (Approx)<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td>Assistant Section Officer<\/td><td>INR 9.8 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Marketing Officer<\/td><td>INR 4.4 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Information Officer<\/td><td>INR 4.4 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Public Relations Officer<\/td><td>INR 3.6 LPA<\/td><\/tr><tr><td>Administrative Officer<\/td><td>INR 3.2 LPA<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sources: AmbitionBox, Indeed<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Top_Recruiters_Hiring_MBAs_in_Marketing_in_India\"><\/span><strong>Top Recruiters Hiring MBAs in Marketing in India<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>MBA graduates with a Marketing specialization are in high demand across various industries for their strong skills and expertise. They also offer high-growth pay packages that increase proportionately with their experience in the industry.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the best recruiters for MBA Marketing graduates in India include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Procter &amp; Gamble (P&amp;G)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Hindustan Unilever\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>ITC Limited\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Deloitte\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Amazon<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"How_to_Plan_Your_Career_Path_After_an_MBA_in_Marketing\"><\/span><strong>How to Plan Your Career Path After an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the best ways to achieve the desired MBA in Sales and Marketing salary, as discussed in this blog, is to plan your career path after graduation carefully. This typically requires aligning your path with your interests, skills, and industry demand, and choosing the right specialization for long-term growth.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Choose your niche area: <\/strong>Within the broader framework of marketing, focus on one area that seems promising for long-term monetary rewards and personal gratification. It could be brand management, sales, digital marketing, or market research, based on your personal strengths, academic interests, and career goals.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Gain hands-on experience: <\/strong>Once you have chosen a specific area of specialization, work on building relevant experience via live real-world projects, internships, and add-on certifications, learning about specialized marketing tools that are in high demand in the industry.<br><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Define your long-term career goals clearly, and set<\/strong> both your short-term and long-term career goals. This would help you target your job search at each stage of your career trajectory and move up the career ladder faster.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Read more:<\/em><\/strong> Career Path after an MBA in Marketing<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career_Scope_MBA_in_Marketing_vs_Other_MBA_Specializations\"><\/span><strong>Career Scope: MBA in Marketing vs Other MBA Specializations&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A helpful exercise for determining the future career prospects of an MBA in Marketing is to conduct a brief comparative analysis of the program with other <a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/blogs\/most-in-demand-mba-specializations\"><strong>MBA specializations<\/strong><\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table\"><table><thead><tr><th><br><strong>MBA<\/strong> <strong>Specialization<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Job Roles<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Average Salary (Approx)<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Key Skills<\/strong><\/th><th><strong>Hiring Industries<\/strong><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-marketing\">MBA in Marketing<\/a><\/td><td>PR Manager<br>Digital Marketing Manager<br>Business Development Manager<\/td><td>INR 7 LPA<\/td><td>Consumer Behavior Analysis<br>Data-Driven Decision-Making Digital Marketing \u00a0<\/td><td>Finance\u00a0<br>Entertainment<br>Advertising<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-healthcare-management-mahe\">MBA in Healthcare Management<\/a><\/td><td>Public Health Manager<br>Healthcare Information Manager<br>Hospital Administrator<\/td><td>INR 8 LPA<\/td><td>People Management<br>Strategic Planning<br>Operational Optimization<\/td><td>Biotechnology<br>Pharmaceuticals<br>Hospitals<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-finance\">MBA in Finance<\/a><\/td><td>Corporate Finance Manager<br>Financial Planner<br>Financial Analyst&nbsp;<\/td><td>INR 7 LPA<\/td><td>Advanced Excel<br>Risk Management<br>Forecasting and Budgeting<\/td><td>Banking&nbsp;<br>Insurance&nbsp;<br>Retail Estate<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-digital-marketing\">MBA in Digital Marketing<\/a><\/td><td>Digital Marketing Manager<br>Performance Marketing Manager<br>Campaign Manager<\/td><td>INR 8 LPA<\/td><td>Data Analytics<br>Performance Measurement<br>Content Management<\/td><td>E-Commerce &amp; Retail<br>EdTech<br>Healthcare<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-analytics-data-science\">MBA in Data Analytics<\/a><\/td><td>Data Analyst<br>Marketing Analyst<br>Analytics Manager<\/td><td>INR 11 LPA<\/td><td>Statistical &amp; Quantitative Skills<br>Data Visualization<br>Data Analysis &amp; Interpretation<\/td><td>E-Commerce<br>FinTech<br>Cybersecurity<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-human-resource-management\">MBA in Human Resource Management<\/a><\/td><td>HR Manager<br>Learning &amp; Development Manager<br>Employee Relations Manager<\/td><td>INR 4.8 LPA<\/td><td>Leadership Ability<br>Managerial Skills<br>Strategic HR Planning<\/td><td>Consulting<br>Hospitality<br>Healthcare&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-project-management\">MBA in Project Management<\/a>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Project Manager<br>Portfolio Manager<br>Agile Project Manager<\/td><td>INR 15 LPA<\/td><td>Risk Management<br>Strategic Planning<br>Agile Methodologies&nbsp;<\/td><td>Construction&nbsp;<br>Consulting&nbsp;<br>Healthcare&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-international-business\">MBA in International Business<\/a><\/td><td>International Trade Manager<br>Global Operations Manager<br>Import Manager<\/td><td>INR 11 LPA<\/td><td>Data Analysis<br>Decision-Making<br>Cross-Cultural Communication<\/td><td>Consulting&nbsp;<br>Travel and Tourism<br>E-Commerce<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-operations-management\">MBA in Operations Management<\/a><\/td><td>Operations Research Analyst<br>Distribution Manager<br>Production Manager<\/td><td>INR 6 LPA<\/td><td>Analytical Decision-Making&nbsp;Strategic Thinking<br>Financial Acumen&nbsp;<\/td><td>Transportation<br>&nbsp;Automotive<br>Manufacturing&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-degree-working-professionals-mahe\">MBA in Supply Chain Management<\/a><\/td><td>Supply Chain Manager<br>Warehouse Manager<br>Supply Chain Analyst<\/td><td>INR 8 LPA<\/td><td>Data Visualization<br>Demand Planning<br>Inventory Management<\/td><td>Retail&nbsp;Manufacturing&nbsp;<br>E-Commerce<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-banking-financial-services-insurance\">MBA in BFSI<\/a>&nbsp;<\/td><td>Corporate Banking Manager<br>Wealth Manager<br>Insurance Manager<\/td><td>INR 8.1 LPA<\/td><td>Financial Modeling<br>Regulatory Compliance<br>Time Management<\/td><td>Corporate Finance<br>Insurance<br>Banking&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-it-fintech\">MBA in IT &amp; FinTech<\/a><\/td><td>IT Manager<br>Cybersecurity Analyst<br>IT Risk Manager<\/td><td>INR 7.7 LPA<\/td><td>AI\/ML<br>Risk Management<br>Strategic Thinking<\/td><td>Banking<br>Cybsercecurity&nbsp;<br>Consulting&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-information-system-management\">MBA in Information System Management<\/a><\/td><td>IT Project Manager<br>IT Strategist<br>Business Systems Analyst<\/td><td>INR 5.7 LPA<\/td><td>Systems Design and Analysis<br>Business Process Optimization<br>Critical Thinking<\/td><td>Automotive&nbsp;<br>Education&nbsp;Finance&nbsp;<\/td><\/tr><tr><td><a href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/online-mba-retail-management\">MBA in Retail Management<\/a><\/td><td>Retail Manager<br>Merchandise Planner<br>E-Commerce Manager<\/td><td>INR 7.3 LPA<\/td><td>Consumer Behavior Analysis<br>Data-Based Decision-Making<br>Inventory Management&nbsp;<\/td><td>E-Commerce<br>FMCG<br>Fashion &amp; Apparel<\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Sources: Glassdoor, Indeed, Payscale<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FAQs\"><\/span><strong>FAQs&nbsp;<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. What is the salary for freshers after an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Entry-level graduates with an MBA in Marketing can apply for roles with a starting salary of INR 3 LPA (approx.). However, this may vary from one professional to another, depending on their skill sets.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Is an MBA in Marketing a good career?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, pursuing an MBA in Marketing is a brilliant career choice, as there is consistently high demand for qualified, skilled marketing graduates across diverse industries and sectors in India.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Is an MBA in Marketing or HR better?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"3\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Both specializations offer their unique benefits to students. There is no single \u201cbetter\u201d choice; it depends on your interests, strengths, and career aspirations.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. Is an MBA in Marketing worth it?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"4\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Absolutely! The course is totally worth it for aspiring learners seeking creative and lucrative career opportunities in multiple industries in India.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. What is the average MBA in Marketing salary?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"5\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The average MBA in Marketing salary in India is estimated at INR 7 LPA (approx). However, this is indicative only and may vary from one professional to another.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>6. Can I become a CEO after an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"6\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, it is possible to advance to a senior role, such as a CEO, after an MBA in Marketing with the right skill set of team management and leadership.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>7. What are 5 careers in Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"7\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The 5 popular career options in the field of Marketing include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Brand Manager<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Marketing Manager<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Digital Marketing Specialist<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Market Analyst<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Content Marketer<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>8. Who is eligible for an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"8\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>To be eligible for the program, students must:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Have a 10 + 2 + 3-year Bachelor\u2019s degree from a recognized university\/institution or an equivalent qualification as recognized by the Association of Indian Universities.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>A minimum of 50% marks in aggregate in graduation (45% for reserved categories).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>9. What job can I get after an MBA in Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"9\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the leading job roles that you can apply for after completing your MBA in Marketing are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Digital Marketing Manager<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Market Research Analyst<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Brand Manager<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sales Manager<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Product Manager<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>10. Which pays more, MBA HR or Marketing?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"10\" class=\"wp-block-list\"><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>The exact pay depends on your skill set and experience. However, on average, an MBA in Marketing tends to pay more than an MBA in HR.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>References:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>https:\/\/in.indeed.com\/career-advice\/finding-a-job\/marketing-job-profiles-after-mba<br>https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/mba-marketing-fresher-salary-SRCH_KO0,21.htm<br>https:\/\/www.glassdoor.co.in\/Salaries\/mba-marketing-salary-SRCH_KO0,13.htm<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/marketing-manager-salary<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/public-relation-officer-salary<br>https:\/\/in.indeed.com\/career\/administrative-officer\/salaries<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/marketing-officer-salary<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/assistant-section-officer-salary<br>https:\/\/www.ambitionbox.com\/profile\/information-officer-salary<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>An MBA in Marketing is one of the most popular course options in India\u2019s competitive business landscape in 2026. The program unlocks promising career prospects for graduates in varied sectors. From digital marketing and brand management to market research and sales leadership, course graduates can explore numerous roles that offer competitive pay packages and strong [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":4,"featured_media":29345878,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[605],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-29345792","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-mba"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v27.5 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/product\/yoast-seo-wordpress\/ -->\n<title>Career After MBA in Marketing: Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"Understand the career scope after an MBA in Marketing, including salary insights and growth prospects in India\u2019s fast-paced, evolving business landscape.\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/www.onlinemanipal.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/29345792\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_GB\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Career After MBA in Marketing: Jobs, Salaries &amp; Scope in India\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Understand the career scope after an MBA in Marketing, incl